classitems.fileoverview:
Bookmark bubble library. This is meant to be included in the
main JavaScript binary of a mobile web application.

Supported browsers: iPhone / iPod / iPad Safari 3.0+

classitems.description: Binds a context object to the function.

params.name: context
params.description: The "this" object to use when the function is run.

classitems.description:
Function used to define an abstract method in a base class. If a subclass
fails to override the abstract method, then an error will be thrown whenever
that method is invoked.

The bubble constructor. Instantiating an object does not cause anything to
be rendered yet, so if necessary you can set instance properties before
showing the bubble.

Handler for the scroll event. Keep a reference to it here, so it can be
unregistered when the bubble is destroyed.
The bubble element.
Whether the bubble has been destroyed.

Shows the bubble if allowed. It is not allowed if:
- The browser is not Mobile Safari, or
- The user has dismissed it too often already, or
- The hash parameter is present in the location hash, or
- The application is in fullscreen mode, which means it was already loaded
  from a homescreen bookmark.

return.description:
True if the bubble is being shown, false if it is not
    allowed to show for one of the aforementioned reasons.

classitems.description:
Shows the bubble if allowed after loading the icon image. This method creates
an image element to load the image into the browser's cache before showing
the bubble to ensure that the image isn't blank. Use this instead of
showIfAllowed if the image url is http and cacheable.
This hack is necessary because Mobile Safari does not properly render
image elements with border-radius CSS.

params.name: opt_callback
params.description:
Closure to be called if and when the bubble
       actually shows.

return.description: True if the bubble is allowed to show.

classitems.description:
Sets the parameter in the location hash. As it is
unpredictable what hash scheme is to be used, this method must be
implemented by the host application.

This gets called automatically when the bubble is shown. The idea is that if
the user then creates a bookmark, we can later recognize on application
startup whether it was from a bookmark suggested with this bubble.

NOTE: Using a hash parameter to track whether the bubble has been shown
conflicts with the navigation system in jQuery Mobile. If you are using that
library, you should implement this function to track the bubble's status in
a different way, e.g. using window.localStorage in HTML5.

Whether the parameter is present in the location hash. As it is
unpredictable what hash scheme is to be used, this method must be
implemented by the host application.

Call this method during application startup if you want to log whether the
application was loaded from a bookmark with the bookmark bubble promotion
parameter in it.

return.description:
Whether the bookmark bubble parameter is present in the
    location hash.

classitems.description:
The number of times the user must dismiss the bubble before we stop showing
it. This is a public property and can be changed by the host application if
necessary.

Time in milliseconds. If the user does not dismiss the bubble, it will auto
destruct after this amount of time.

The prefix for keys in local storage. This is a public property and can be
changed by the host application if necessary.
The key name for the dismissed state.
The arrow image in base64 data url format.
The close image in base64 data url format.

The link used to locate the application's home screen icon to display inside
the bubble. The default link used here is for an iPhone home screen icon
without gloss. If your application uses a glossy icon, change this to
'apple-touch-icon'.
Regular expression for detecting an iPhone or iPod or iPad.
Regular expression for detecting an iPad.
Regular expression for extracting the iOS version. Only matches 2.0 and up.

Whether the user has dismissed the bubble often enough

return.description: Whether the application is running in fullscreen mode.

classitems.description: Whether the application is running inside Mobile Safari.

classitems.description: Whether the application is running on an iPad.

return.description: True if the current user agent looks like an iPad.

classitems.description: Creates a version number from 4 integer pieces between 0 and 127 (inclusive).

Positions the bubble at the bottom of the viewport using an animated
transition.

Destroys the bubble by removing its DOM nodes from the document, and
remembers that it was dismissed.
Gets called after a while if the user ignores the bubble.
Gets the y offset used to show the bubble (i.e., position it on-screen).
Gets the y offset used to hide the bubble (i.e., position it off-screen).
The url of the app's bookmark icon.

Scrapes the document for a link element that specifies an Apple favicon and
returns the icon url. Returns an empty data url if nothing can be found.
Gets the requested link tag if it exists.

params.description: The rel attribute of the link tag to get.

return.description: The requested link tag or null.
